a terrific li'l album that evokes a fun period and flick for those of us who came of age when `` urban cowboy '' introduced john travolta to the world in his third iconic dance-man starring role ( after saturday night fever and grease ) in a productive three-year period , this soundtrack is an essential . we 're all familiar with the big hits that populated this disc and dominated top 40 radio in the early '80s , but i 'd buy it solely for the haunting duet by linda ronstadt and j.d . souther , `` hearts against the wind , '' that closes the show